    "description": {
      "es": "",
      "en": "Returns the current global process times. The return value is an object with five attributes: user - user time system - system time children_user - user time of all child processes children_system - system time of all child processes elapsed - elapsed real time since a fixed point in the past For backwards compatibility, this object also behaves like a five-tuple containing user, system, children_user, children_system, and elapsed in that order. See the Unix manual page times(2) and times(3) ..."
